  "prompt": "Which party is most likely to win the upcoming election in Punjab?",
  "response": "As of my last update, it's challenging to predict with certainty which party will win the upcoming election in Punjab, India, as elections can be influenced by many factors including current political climate, candidate popularity, and local issues. However, I can provide some context based on recent trends.\n\nIn the 2017 Punjab Legislative Assembly election, the Indian National Congress (INC) secured a majority, winning 77 out of 117 seats. The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) and the Shiromani Akali Dal (SAD), which contested in alliance with the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), won 20 and 18 seats respectively.\n\nFor the upcoming election, political analysts are closely watching the performance of these parties, with a particular focus on AAP's increased activities and organizational efforts in the state. Additionally, BJP's decision to contest independently from SAD could impact vote distribution.\n\nTo get the most accurate and current predictions, it would be beneficial to consult recent polls and analyses from local political experts and news sources as the election date approaches.",
